<Author>NLoGalway
<Content>Unbelievable!! My boyfriend and I stayed here for 3 nights in February 2008.Arrival: we took the air france shuttle bus from the airport to the Arc de Triomphe. The hotel is about a 5 min walk from there but make sure to get the right directions! I think you must walk down avenue de hoche and then turn right onto rue de courcelles and you will see the hotel in front of you! On arrival the doormen whisked our way bags and were extremely friendly, even complementing my pathetic attempt at speaking french!! Our room was not ready when we arrived as it was early but we went to the bar for 30 mins until it was ready.Room: Very spacious with big comfy bed! Television had good selection of channels sky news etc... Lovely fluffy dressing gown and slippers also. Probably the best part of the room was the view from our large windows; onto the courtyard. We were only on the 2nd floor but it was beautiful!Staff: The staff were abolutely fantastic! They even remembered our name and preffered drinks in the bar! Consieierge quite good although perhaps not as friendly as the rest! Doormen excellent!Facilities: The Purple Bar was lovely. We drank here most evenings and although it is quite expensive the staff make up for it! They are so friendly! Also on the thursday evening of our stay, the bar seemed to be packed full of business people having a great time-really good atmosphere for paris!! We did not use the restaurant or have breakfast there so cannot comment. Also we didnt avail of spa as we did not have time!Location: As mentioned before, the hotel is situated very near the Arc de Triomphe/Champs Elysee! We even walked to the Eiffel Tower one evening (about 20 mins walk). For eveything else we used taxis and the metro. The metro stop of Courcelles is 3 min walk from hotel and very easy to use! Not alot of restaurants in immediate area around hotel but many within walking distance. There is a lovely little cafe across from the hotel for crossants etc...All in all we had a truely amazing time in Paris,and this hotel definitely had alot to do with it! I would definitely recommend this hotel to everyone and anyone, it is one of the best hotels I have stayed in abroad! Hope this review was helpful! 
