<Content>OK Hotel, OK Location Used Hilton points for a two-night hotel stay. Asked for an upper-level garden view room. Best shower ever, but bathroom was a bit small and lacked counter space. Bed covers and linens were clean, but the carpet definitely needs to be replaced in the rooms and the halls. Lobby was impressive. Staff was very attentive and helpful. Asked about using a pre-paid calling card from the room but was informed we'd be charged twice -- once with the card and once by the hotel. Not sure if that would have been true or not. Did not eat at the hotel. Instead found a very nice outdoor cafe if you walk left out of the hotel and further up the block, pastry, wine and cheese shops. Take the train from CDG to Gard du Nord to avoid traffic, but then take a taxi to the hotel -- too trying to do that with luggage. 
