<Content>It's not a cheap hotel - so your bed has a mattress. After we fled the 2-star nightmare hotel we'd booked we came here. It was plenty more expensive - but then you get a good hotel. Art-deco style. The standard room we had was rendered smallish by the crib we needed. Clean and bright. Very comfortable bed. Great water pressure. AIR CONDITIONING which you won't find in a lot of hotels. The mini-bar was outrageously priced at 6 Euro for a small water, so BYOW. The location is okay - not my personal preference as I like the Marais district - but it's a short walk to the upscale shopping on the Champs Elysses and the traffic extravaganza they call Arc de Triomph. They want 26 Euro for a bare-bones breakfast, so plan on eating elsewhere unless you're Spendy McSpenderson. 
