<Content>Great place We stayed here during the French Open and were pleasantly surprised to see many of the players choosing to stay here as well. We had a room on the 6th floor which gives you access to the executive lounge, so we enjoyed the complimentary breakfast and snacks/drinks that were available throughout the day. We found the concierge to be very helpful. Never felt that it was snobbish at all. The hotel is located in a quiet, safe area and there are two convenient Metro stops: one with a 8-10 minute walk, the other a 10-12 minute walk. There is not much to do around the hotel, but the Metro is so easy to use, that we spent our days out and about and then returned to the quiet of the hotel and relaxed in the executive lounge. The room was very nicely done and a good size for European hotel. Ours overlooked the courtyard, so it was very peaceful as well. I would stay here again. 
