<Content>Heavenly 25th Wedding Anniversary We spent 3 nights here as part of our anniversary and had a wonderful time. The facilities are new and well maintained. Great bed, top notch shower and bathtub, absolutely outstanding concierge desk and hotel staff - we literally had a laughing crowd load our baggage into our rental car as we left. The bar and restaurant were excellent, and Carlos the bartender is helpful and friendly (tell him that you heard about him on the Internet). The hotel exterior is rather dull, but the interior and your room are clean, new, and luxurious.As far as the comments on its location, LOOK at a map! We found the hotel as a great base of operations; it's a short walk to the Arc de Triomphe, metro, Champs d'Elysee, buses, great restaurants, and shopping. It is in a very safe and quiet financial/diplomatic district. It is not at the Seine or the Eiffel Tower, but a brief cab ride will get you there quickly, or better yet enjoy a pleasant and romantic walk. Do take the Air France bus from Charles DeGaulle to the Arc de Triomphe, and walk a few blocks to the hotel. Do consider paying for the upgrade to executive class for the lounge, which has great food and drink available - we had a great breakfast daily, and occasionally used the available snacks as a meal replacement. Do ask the concierge/staff for help and suggestions - buy your Louvre and other museum tickets here to avoid lines - we took their advice and explored the newly opened Musee de l'Orangerie of Impressionist art, and went to a nearby bistro as recommended.Most importantly, do explore the wonders of Paris. We also spent time at the Paris Hilton for a different base of operations and experience and would also recommend it. 
