<Content>Sterile, snooty, outrageously expensive. Sterile, snooty, outrageously expensive. Rooms ok, the usual Hilton experience only with a French attitude. Which is why I still have to give it above average. The kids in the business center were terrific. No view to speak of. $30 for continental, $45 for full breakfast. $9 for a half cup of caf茅 au lait. Why it was only a half cup -- ?? I鈥榤 a bit of a cheapskate, but that seemed way out of line. There is a small bistro across the street with a very nice $12 breakfast including coffee to your liking. The hotel is quite a walk from anything of interest, use the busses and subway. NOTE TO RYAN AIR passengers. The RyanAir facility is at Beauvais a 45 minute taxi drive. I found a private car shuttle for $47, just Google it a day in advance and make a reservation. The Ryan Air folks let me slide on my luggage weight coming out of Lubeck, but nailed me good out of France.An observation about TripAdvisor (if you鈥檝e seen this in other of my posts, feel free to skip): I used it extensively when planning a last-minute 3-week trip to Europe, was very happy to have the service and felt I should pay back with my comments. I think you have to read between the lines and determine the type of traveler writing the review compared to your own type. I鈥檝e stayed in places that were highly recommended and turned out to be terrible; and the reverse. Try to judge whether the contributor is complaining about a one-time, bad experience as a result of an inattentive employee as opposed to a basic fault with the property itself. If a restaurant manager was rude, so what. If the place floods, and smells -- that鈥檚 a different story. 
